Revert "Add the dummy certificate"

This reverts commit e3459746607187f53e0cc68259ce6980b43f2fc3.
Ansible does not allow to simply and cleanly override file in an other
playbook, so this was a bad idea.
Add the dummy certificate
Remove deprecated notation
Correct the rabbitmq configuration
Add info in the README
Refresh apt-cache after adding rabbitmq repo
Better organisation
Better variable for template
Add ssl, config, restart
Add a handler to restart rabbitmq
Update the vars to be valid
Basic playbook, just install and copy a basic config
Initial commit
updates
Make travis install the last Ansible
Update the CHANGELOG to follow Keep a CHANGELOG format

Make user permissions configurable. Fixes #39

Signed-off-by: Stefan van Wouw <stefanvanwouw@gmail.com>

Get the configuration template to generate a clean configuration.

The templates is still pretty complex, but at least the configuration
file that get generated is well formed.
Bump version number
Add a test to ensure RabbitMQ is listenning to the good port by default
Fix the way the Redhat installation is included

Change item.name to item.vhost. Fix #31

Since the dict option is `vhost` it make more sense for this hash item
to be named like that.

Note that it was previously named like that, but it changed silently in
a commit before. So I consider this a bug.

Moved install to install/main

Tried to prevent us having too many files in a single directory.  This layout
feels a bit more natural.

Update the test part to show how to change the vagrant VM
Merge branch 'pr_14'. Add support for Redhat
Avoid always vagrant with Centos

We will have to rely on vagrant to test the cluster, but this should give us
good coverage on standalone and validate syntax.

Merge pull request #17

* Prepare the playbook for clustering support
* Add test for the standalone installation
Flush handlers before tests begin + rebase
Updated with new changes from master

Added tests for basic standalone install

* Preparing for clustering work.
* Renamed the Vagrant host to standalone so we can add a set of nodes for
  clustering.
* Removed the rabbitmq_policy this is now in upstream ansible.
* Moved attributes from the Vagrantfile to params in the playbook.
* Added integration tests for this baseline functionality.
Fix README chapter importance
Add a section about installation and versionning in the README

Merge branch 'pr_8'

Conflicts:
	vars/test.yml

Fix the test VM which was not listening anywhere

The test configuration was turning off the SSL listener, but since there
was no TCP address listener given in the test configuration RabbitMQ was
running without any listening address.
Disable tcp listener if address is blank

README Fixes: server cert var, typo, and some quoting
Fix quoting and a typo in README
Fix server cert var name in README

Enable the RabbitMQ service on boot by default

Rabbit doesn't enable itself on boot

Updated handler to enable the service when installed.

Merge pull request #9 from retr0h/retr0h/cleanup-vagrant

Updated to integrate with vagrant cleaner
Correctly escaped the pluralization
Update the README to match the last variable change
Remove rabbitmq_env by detecting if rabbitmq_conf_env is defined or not

Updated to integrate with vagrant cleaner

* Configured vagrant provision to execute as a role so defaults are properly
  loaded.
* Moved test vars to Vagrantfile explicit loading
* No longer need to ignore `vagrant_ansible_inventory_default` with a newer
  version of Vagrant.
* Updated Vagrant file to conform to Rubocop syntax.
Fixing whitespace.
Adding support for non-default nodes
Adding an entry in defaults/main for rabbitmq-env.conf support.
Adding support for rabbitmq-env.conf
Set default value for vhost and users definition
Add README section about plugins
Ignore .vagrant folder
Update test file
Support disabling of all plugins when the list is empty
Add support for a new_only option
Add support of plugin enable/disable
Prevent the deactivation of all other plugins when federation is activated
Force the hostname in the Vagrantfile
Ensure that rabbitmq is running before changing vhost

Merge pull request #5 from gaqzi/optional-ssl

Add an option to not use SSL listener

Add an option to not use SSL listener

The use case for this is if the server is running internally and not
connected to the internet, there is simply no need for SSL.

The default has been set add a SSL listener and matches the current
behavior.

Make force configurable when adding users

I re-use the same username for staging/production vhosts and having the
user re-created every time drops the vhost configuration for the first
configured host. By allowing the option to be configured I can keep the
same username for both hosts.

The default value set matches the old default.

Add the possibility to federate instances

Split vhost configuration in vhost.yml
Align variable in main.yml
Add a variable to set the  option
Allow to the user to define SSL certificate name

Corrects the vhost definition

The "/" was not needed and was interfering by being added in the name of
the vhost.
Separate users from vhost in the configuration

Various modification to make the playbook Glaxy friendly

* Add the meta folder

This closes #1.

Remove TCP listenning by default

SSL listenning is now the default configuration. *NOT USING SSL IS BAD
MOKAYY?*
